WEBVTT

00:00.333 --> 00:02.801
Libby:  <i>Previously on</i>
<i>masters of sex...</i>

00:02.803 --> 00:04.336
You sleep with
your mouth open.

00:04.338 --> 00:07.606
We don't sleep here.
Get dressed.

00:07.608 --> 00:09.708
I saw them last night
leaving the hotel.

00:09.710 --> 00:11.877
<i>How did I not know</i>
<i>they're sleeping together?</i>

00:11.879 --> 00:15.614
I've shared nearly
everything with you.

00:15.616 --> 00:17.182
You should share with me.

00:17.184 --> 00:18.751
Lillian,
I'm not that interesting.

00:18.753 --> 00:21.220
Dr. Masters,
I don't have lice,
I swear.

00:21.222 --> 00:25.090
If you won't sit down, leave.
And you won't be welcome back.

00:25.092 --> 00:27.659
You couldn't have kids?
Why didn't you tell me?

00:27.661 --> 00:29.962
You never would have
married me then.

00:29.964 --> 00:31.497
Tatti greathouse
just called.

00:31.499 --> 00:33.499
<i>She said that</i>
<i>you were fired.</i>

00:33.501 --> 00:34.666
Dr. Greathouse:
No hospital in the midwest

00:34.668 --> 00:36.935
Will even let you
step through their doors.

00:36.937 --> 00:42.241
Why do I have to
hear everything about
my husband thirdhand?

00:42.243 --> 00:44.209
You just have to
trust me right now.

00:44.211 --> 00:47.780
I feel comfortable in speaking
for my partner when I say

00:47.782 --> 00:54.686
How pleased we both are
to be bringing our
work here, together.

00:56.923 --> 00:59.625
(theme music playing)

01:50.977 --> 01:52.644
Virginia: Do you
think he's dreaming?

01:52.646 --> 01:55.481
Libby: I read once that
dogs dream of running

01:55.483 --> 01:57.216
In great open spaces.

01:57.218 --> 01:59.151
How would
they test for that?

01:59.153 --> 02:01.153
In animals or babies?

02:01.155 --> 02:04.990
Are you sure it's okay
that we stopped by this way?

02:04.992 --> 02:06.325
Of course it's okay.

02:06.327 --> 02:07.059
You know how it is.

02:07.061 --> 02:09.962
I was just driving around,
trying to get him to sleep,

02:09.964 --> 02:13.198
And suddenly there we were,
outside your front door.

02:13.200 --> 02:14.433
It's good to see you.

02:14.435 --> 02:16.735
He has much more hair
than last time.

02:16.737 --> 02:19.671
You haven't seen
him in a while.

02:19.673 --> 02:22.641
And I'm sorry for that,
libby. I've been...

02:22.643 --> 02:25.410
You've been busy.
No, I understand.

02:25.412 --> 02:28.714
I wish bill were the type
to show off baby pictures.

02:28.716 --> 02:32.484
I did put one in his
wallet, just in case.

02:32.486 --> 02:35.821
I haven't seen
much of bill either.

02:35.823 --> 02:38.223
That's going
to change, right?

02:40.093 --> 02:43.295
I have to admit, gin,
I was shocked by the news.

02:43.297 --> 02:46.431
Just completely
caught off guard.

02:46.433 --> 02:49.334
Do they know at maternity?

02:49.636 --> 02:51.003
Uh...

02:51.005 --> 02:53.338
About what you two
are doing?

02:53.873 --> 02:56.708
You haven't given
dr. Depaul notice?

02:58.511 --> 02:59.578
Not yet.

02:59.580 --> 03:02.214
I don't blame you waiting
to see if this sticks.

03:02.216 --> 03:04.550
A third hospital
in as many months?

03:04.552 --> 03:07.686
I understand
why it's enticing to him.

03:07.688 --> 03:10.155
To have the study
readily accepted

03:10.157 --> 03:12.457
After the resistance
at memorial.

03:12.459 --> 03:13.592
(stammers) don't take this
the wrong way,

03:13.594 --> 03:18.063
Because baby john
was born there and
I received excellent care.

03:18.065 --> 03:20.332
But bill going to work
at buell green?

03:20.334 --> 03:23.635
I cannot understand it.
Can you?

03:24.103 --> 03:25.571
It's quite a surprise.

03:25.573 --> 03:27.673
He's not just
rolling downhill,
gini,

03:27.675 --> 03:29.041
He's picking up speed.

03:29.043 --> 03:31.109
From chief of obstetrics
at maternity,

03:31.111 --> 03:33.245
To taking a staff position
at memorial,

03:33.247 --> 03:36.114
To walking out and heading
to the negro hospital?

03:36.116 --> 03:38.150
I don't know
what to say, libby.

03:38.152 --> 03:41.820
Where to from here?
The state penitentiary?

03:53.199 --> 03:55.434
(keys clinking)

04:01.674 --> 04:03.308
Have you eaten?

04:03.409 --> 04:05.677
I'm not hungry.

04:08.047 --> 04:11.783
Your way of saying,
"let's skip dinner
and move to dessert?"

04:11.785 --> 04:14.886
Look again,
it's not what you think.

04:14.888 --> 04:19.424
It's the key to
your new office
at buell green.

04:19.426 --> 04:20.525
Not the obvious choice,
I admit.

04:20.527 --> 04:24.196
But they're a fine hospital,
open to new things,

04:24.198 --> 04:27.799
They fully endorse the study
and my bringing you aboard.

04:27.801 --> 04:32.170
That seems like
a decision you could've
discussed with me first.

04:32.172 --> 04:33.905
Maybe. But timing aside,

04:33.907 --> 04:37.542
This is fabulous news.
Calls for a toast.

04:37.544 --> 04:38.277
Uh...

04:38.279 --> 04:40.379
We can finally
get back to work.

04:40.381 --> 04:45.284
And you can stop selling
those ridiculous diet pills.

04:46.653 --> 04:47.252
I'm sorry, bill.

04:47.254 --> 04:51.223
How did you see
me coming aboard
at buell green?

04:51.225 --> 04:52.557
What do you mean?

04:52.559 --> 04:54.459
I mean, as what?

04:54.461 --> 04:56.428
What is my official title?

04:56.430 --> 04:58.397
My responsibilities?
My salary?

04:58.399 --> 05:01.099
We work all that out,
of course.

05:01.101 --> 05:01.967
When?

05:01.969 --> 05:08.140
I'd like to know those
things before I decide
to upend my life.

05:08.508 --> 05:11.910
I want to be very clear
on what you're offering me.

05:11.912 --> 05:15.514
How about an opportunity
to finish what we started?

05:15.516 --> 05:16.748
How about the study?

05:16.750 --> 05:21.953
I would just
like the specifics
spelled out, ahead of time.

05:22.655 --> 05:24.122
In writing.

05:26.626 --> 05:28.260
I see.

05:28.262 --> 05:30.362
As I've proven
myself untrustworthy.

05:30.364 --> 05:34.299
Because I have two children
I'm supporting.

05:34.301 --> 05:35.834
If you end up
leaving this hospital,

05:35.836 --> 05:39.004
Like you left the last one
and the one before that,

05:39.006 --> 05:43.175
What guarantee do I have
they will keep me on
without you?

05:43.177 --> 05:46.778
I don't have the luxury
of jumping ship on a whim.

05:46.780 --> 05:50.615
I don't have the luxury
of not selling those
ridiculous diet pills.

05:50.617 --> 05:54.019
I don't understand.
You shouldn't assume
I'll just come

05:54.021 --> 05:56.488
Running whenever
you call, bill.

05:56.490 --> 05:58.123
I do have other opportunities.

05:58.125 --> 06:00.258
And they are?
I'd like to know.

06:00.260 --> 06:04.363
What opportunities
do you have outside
of diet pills?

06:04.365 --> 06:05.430
A job with lillian.

06:05.432 --> 06:09.234
She's doing very
important work.
Work I'm very much part of.

06:09.236 --> 06:11.803
I'm sure she'd make it
worth my while to stay.

06:11.805 --> 06:14.239
I don't think
you want to
play that hand.

06:14.241 --> 06:14.840
It's not a hand.

06:14.842 --> 06:19.544
I don't think lillian
regards you quite
as highly as you think.

06:19.645 --> 06:23.548
Why do you say that?
She knows about us.

06:24.183 --> 06:26.952
About the work we're doing.

06:28.187 --> 06:29.821
Upstairs.

06:33.793 --> 06:36.762
Gene, your side of the bed
is gonna turn to stone

06:36.764 --> 06:39.965
If you don't start
sleeping in it again.

06:41.768 --> 06:43.502
(sighs)

